Context: The School of Health Services Management offers specialized medical administrative programs at George Brown College's Waterfront Campus at the Daphne Cockwell Centre for Health Sciences. Graduates find work in medical environments such as hospitals, clinics, dental and medical offices. Program options are matched with students' skills, background, and career goals through the Entry Advising service. Free information sessions are available to learn more about the programs and have questions answered by faculty and staff. The college provides a land acknowledgment statement and keeps students informed about application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, tours, and more via sign up. Contact information: 416-415-2000, TTY: 1-877-515-5559, ask.george@georgebrown.ca, Social Media Hub. Students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements and note that the information on the website is subject to change without notice.
